@/bcd-to-dec.description: Converts a packed binary coded decimal byte into a byte value in range [0, 99]

@/bitwise-and.description: Computes bitwise AND of two or more bytes. A resulting bit at a particular position is 1 only if corresponding bits of all inputs are 1.

@/bitwise-not.description: Computes bitwise NOT of a byte. Also known as complement. A resulting bit at a particular position is 1 when input bit at the same position is 0, and vice versa.

@/bitwise-or.description: Computes bitwise OR of two or more bytes. A resulting bit at a particular position is 0 only if all corresponding bits of inputs are 0.

@/bitwise-xor.description: Computes bitwise XOR of two or more bytes. A resulting bit at a particular position is 1 only if an odd number of corresponding bits of inputs is 1.

@/dec-to-bcd.description: Converts a byte value in range [0, 99] into a packed binary coded decimal byte

@/f32-to-number.description: Converts 32-bit IEEE-754 encoded floating point number presented as four bytes to a number. A result of the conversion will be in range between -3.4E+38 to 3.4E+38 with an accuracy of 7 digits. It means, a float number greater than seven digits in length will be inaccurate and lose a fractional part.

@/i16-to-number.description: Converts 16-bit signed integer presented as two bytes to a number. A result of the conversion will be between -32768.00 and 32767.00.

@/i32-to-number.description: Converts 32-bit signed integer presented as four bytes to a number. A result of the conversion will be between -2147483600.00 and 2147483600.00.

@/i8-to-number.description: Converts 8-bit signed integer presented as one byte to a number. A result of the conversion will be between -128.00 and 127.00.

@/number-to-f32.description: Converts a number to 32-bit IEEE-754 encoded floating point number presented as four bytes. An input for the the conversion should be between -3.4E+38 to 3.4E+38 with an accuracy of 7 digits. It means, a float number greater than seven digits in length will be inaccurate and lose a fractional part.

@/number-to-i16.description: Converts number to a 16-bit signed integer presented as 2 bytes. An input for the the conversion should be between -32768.00 and 32767.00.

@/number-to-i32.description: Converts number to a 32-bit signed integer presented as 4 bytes. An input for the the conversion should be between -2147483600.00 and 2147483600.00.

@/number-to-i8.description: Converts number to a 8-bit signed integer presented as one byte. An input for the the conversion should be between -128.00 and 127.00.

@/number-to-u16.description: Converts number to a 16-bit unsigned integer presented as 2 bytes. An input for the the conversion should be between 0.00 and 65535.00.

@/number-to-u32.description: Converts number to a 32-bit unsigned integer presented as 4 bytes. An input for the the conversion should be between 0.00 and 4294967000.00.

@/number-to-u8.description: Converts number to a 8-bit unsigned integer presented as one byte. An input for the the conversion should be between 0.00 and 255.00.

HkjNO_xxz.description: Input number. Interpreted as a signed 32-bit interger

HylHuulxf.description: Shift bits count. Truncated to an integer. Negative values round to zero
HylHuulxf.label: N

@/shift-left.description: Performs logical left-shift of `IN` by `N` bits.

BkvUuuleG.description: Shift bits count. Truncated to an integer. Negative values round to zero
BkvUuuleG.label: N

rkXLOulgz.description: Input number. Interpreted as a signed 32-bit interger

@/shift-right.description: Performs logical right-shift of `IN` by `N` bits.

@/u16-to-number.description: Converts 16-bit unsigned integer presented as two bytes to a number. A result of the conversion will be between 0.00 and 65535.00.

@/u32-to-number.description: Converts 32-bit unsigned integer presented as four bytes to a number. A result of the conversion will be between 0.00 and 4294967000.00.

@/u8-to-number.description: Converts 8-bit unsigned integer presented as one byte to a number. A result of the conversion will be between 0.00 and 255.00.
